SIMPLE: entanglement
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Entanglement
<hw>En*tan"gle*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>State of being entangled; intricate and confused involution; that
which entangles; intricacy; perplexity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>An extensive low obstacle formed
of stakes, stumps, or the like, connected by wires, ropes, or the
like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>An obstruction of cables and
spars across a river or harbor entrance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Entangler</ent>⟦br⟧
